conclusion: Need to analyze the v-t graphs for both cars and calculate the distance each car has traveled by t = 10 s.
Car A has a constant velocity of 40 m/s from t = 0 s to t = 30 s.
Car B starts from rest and its velocity increases linearly, reaching 40 m/s at t = 20 s.
Distance traveled by Car A from t = 0 s to t = 10 s is 400 m.
Car B's velocity increases linearly from 0 m/s to 20 m/s at t = 10 s.
Distance traveled by Car B from t = 0 s to t = 10 s is 100 m.
At t = 10 s, Car A has traveled 400 m while Car B has traveled 100 m.
Car A is ahead of Car B at t = 10 s because Car A has traveled a greater distance (400 m) compared to Car B (100 m).
